      • GeneInfoRecord

        public GeneInfoRecord(java.lang.String taxon,
              java.lang.String entrez,
              java.lang.String officialSymbol,
              java.lang.String defaultSymbol,
              java.lang.String officialName,
              java.lang.String defaultName,
              java.lang.String mapLocation,
              java.lang.String geneType,
              java.lang.String locusTag)
        Construct information from file for one gene.
        Parameters:
        taxon - the organism
        entrez - NCBI gene number
        officialSymbol - official symbol if present, e.g. from HGNC
        defaultSymbol - the NCBI symbol, may be the same as officialSymbol
        officialName - official name if present, e.g. from HGNC
        defaultName - NCBI name, may be the same as the officialName
        mapLocation - chromosome band of the gene, if known
        geneType - e.g. protein-coding, ncrna, etc.
        locusTag - treefam uses this field to identify yeast
